text.section:
A child may be taken into custody under this subtitle by any of the following methods:
Pursuant to an order of the court;
By a law enforcement officer pursuant to the law of arrest;
By a law enforcement officer or other person authorized by the court if the officer or other person has reasonable grounds to believe that the child is in immediate danger from the child's surroundings and that the child's removal is necessary for the child's protection;
By a law enforcement officer or other person authorized by the court if the officer or other person has reasonable grounds to believe that the child has run away from the child's parents, guardian, or legal custodian; or
In accordance with § 3-8A-14.1 of this subtitle.
